       <p><h5>TECHTSAR:</h5></p>
        <p>Techsar is the Technical Festival of the B.Sc. IT department.This fest is organized by the SY.BSC.IT Students with the help of students volunteered by FY.BSC.IT . Last year it was organized on 9th January, 2020. Events like Logo Making, Fast Typing, Fun Games, PowerPoint Presentation, Web designing, TechHacks, Games Strom, Movie Making, Blind Typing, Typography, Assembling and dissembling and Photography etc were arranged during this event.Many Students from more than 50 different colleges take part in this event.</p>
    
        <p><h5>NATIONAL SERVICE SCHEME (N.S.S.):</h5></p>
        <p>NSS volunteers helped physically disabled voters from Colaba to reach polling station during Loksabha elections 2019.Students are encouraged to join NSS which contribute significantly towards preparing the youth committed to serving the nation. Those who complete 120 hours of work in these activities are eligible for additional 10 marks as per University rules. Dr. S.G. Thakur is in-charge and Shri. Kalan, Smt. Sheetal Panchikar, Smt. Jaya Pawar & Kum.Benita Rodrigues are members of the committee. In 2015-16 NSS committee has organized more than 20 activities for the students.</p>
    
    <p>NSS Department of Elphinstone College organised a 'Free Health Check Up Camp' for Students and Staff members on 23/08/2019 in the College Staff room. More than 200 students and 80 staff members availed the opportunity. Respected Principal Dr. Madhuri Kagalkar ma'am graced the camp and motivated the students for the cause.</p>
<p>NSS Department of Elphinstone College organised live streaming of address by Hon'ble Prime Minister Shri Narendra Modiji on the occasion of 'Fit India' for Students and Staff members on 29/08/2019. More than 200 students and 60 staff members attended the live streaming session.</p>
   
